dct_description_sm: United States Coast and Geodetic Survey.
Relief shown by contours and spot heights; depths shown by soundings and isolines.
"Triangulation, topography, and inside hydrography by A.W. Chase, Assistant in 1875; off-shore hydrography by Lieut. E.H.C. Leutze, U.S.N. Assistant in 1878."
Oriented with north toward upper right.
Contour interval 20 ft.; soundings in feet.
Series no. 670 is crossed out and 5134 is stamped as the new number.
